[src:information-theory/channel-capacity] This result is known as the **Shannon–Hartley theorem**.
[src:information-theory/channel-capacity] When the SNR is large (SNR ≫ 0 dB), the capacity $C\approx W\log _{2}{\frac {\bar {P}}{N_{0}W}}$ is logarithmic in power and approximately linear in bandwidth.
[src:information-theory/channel-capacity] This is called the *bandwidth-limited regime*.
[src:information-theory/channel-capacity] When the SNR is small (SNR ≪ 0 dB), the capacity $C\approx {\frac {\bar {P}}{N_{0}\ln 2}}$ is linear in power but insensitive to bandwidth.
[src:information-theory/channel-capacity] This is called the *power-limited regime*.
